history.content:
I took CS170 and CS189 concurrently with some other classes and did fine. If that's all you need to take you will be able to handle it!

That said if you don't want to risk it, probably 170/168 is better as 170 is a lot more crucial than 189.
I took CS170 and CS189 concurrently with some other classes and did fine. If that's all you need to take you will be able to handle it!

I was wondering what classes I should take for my last semester. So far I have taken CS 162, CS 186, CS 188, and am currently in CS 160 for the summer. I have also taken Geography C188 (Geographic Information Systems) for 4 units of my tech electives. 
This fall I had planned to take CS 168 and CS 161, but am thinking I may regret not taking CS 189 or CS 170. I would like to work in software engineering when I graduate and I feel like not taking CS 170 would leave me at a big disadvantage when I start looking for jobs. At the same time, Machine Learning is very popular right now and not taking that I might regret later as well. 
The advising website for upper-division CS requirements suggests not taking 170 and 189 in combination so I am thinking if I try to switch, I will only switch one of my classes (probably 161). Full disclosure, I was enrolled in CS 170 last spring but had to late drop the class because I fell to far behind.
Can anyone offer any guidance on how to decide?
history.subject: What 2 final CS classes to take
